anja krieger stanford department of classics skip to navigation department of classics standford university logo header home people programs courses projects news events resources contact anja krieger contact information anjak stanford edu biography anja is a graduate student in the archaeology track having studied at the university of freiburg and the universita degli studi di perugia she recieved her ma from the university of heidelberg in 2011 writing a thesis about the role of seafaring in homer's odyssey and hesiod's works and days she explored the status function and motivation of seafaring in these works and supplemented the evidence of the literary sources with an analysis of ship representations on late geometric vases she is particularly interested in seafaring and maritime trade and the interdisciplinary research on networks across the mediterranean and on cultural exchange with a focus on late bronze and iron age greece her interests include greek epigraphy latin elegy aegean prehistory and mediterrranean archaeology email stanford classics find us on facebook address & phone search upcoming events q&a with spartacus creator steven deknight 02 23 2012 james rives animal sacrifice and social relations in judaea and rome 03 07 2012 see more site info 2012 stanford university department of classics all rights reserved site design by chapter three login login with sunet speaker request webform for faculty stanford classics wikisite powered by drupal an open source content management system
